data.text: Cadbury Research Library Special Collections Muirhead Tower University of Birmingham Edgbaston Birmingham B15 2TT United Kingdom Cadbury Research Library : Special Collections Personal and Family Papers This is a list of personal papers of individuals and families held in Special Collections at the University of Birmingham, UK as at April 2012. A separate list is available of our holdings of papers of organizations. Our collections include papers of politicians, musicians, writers, novelists and poets, missionaries and clergymen. Other personal archives relate to the history of medicine, athletics, performing arts and the First and Second World Wars. Also well represented are travel diaries, diaries of women, and family letters. Abernethy, John (1764–1831), surgeon: surgical lectures, 1802–03. Finding No: MS716 A Abrahams, Harold Maurice (1899–1978), athlete and athletics administrator: papers, 1936–76. Finding No: HA Acton, Philip (fl 1876–1891): verse, 1876–91. Finding No: MS568 Adam, George Mair (1898–1989), athletics administrator: papers. Finding No: GA Adams, Margaret (b 1912) calligrapher: calligraphic specimens, 20th century. Finding No: MS229 Adams, William Henry Davenport (1828–1891), writer: poems and songs, 1847. Finding No: MS373 Adcock, Ernest E. (fl 1913-1944), organ historian: notebooks, albums of cuttings, photograph albums, mid 20th cent. Finding No: BOA Adcock, William (fl 1816–1817) of Birmingham: poems, 1816–17. Finding No: MS578 Aldous, William (b 1789) of London: diary, 1862–64. Finding No: MS133 Allason, Henry (fl 1784–1802) of Virginia: note book, 1784–1802. Finding No: MS781 Allen, Ianthe Theodora Heron- (fl 1910–1924) of Selsey Bill, Sussex: theatre programmes and playbills, 1910–24.
